== Etymology == The name "Segiri" is coined by [[Sena]] after she had brought No. 7 some onigiri as a peace offering, as she did not wish to refer to her as a number. Segiri is a combination of "Se" from her name, No. 7, and "giri" from the onigiri.
Similar portmanteaus exist for her names in other languages as well. For example, in Japanese, her name "Nagiri" comes from ''"Nana"'', the word for the number seven, and ''"giri"'' from onigiri.
== Trivia == * Onigiri becomes her favorite food after having it introduced to her. * She is the youngest Hero in {{XC3|-}}. * The number seven is often seen as a lucky number in many cultures. This contrasts with No. 13, whose namesake is often seen as unlucky.
